----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

B. IMPLEMENTATION:

--------------------------------------------------------------------
Q1.  There are 2 microcontrollers in the mbed LPC1768 board: (1) the LPC1768 microcontroller containing the Cortex-M3 CPU, and (2) the USB-interface microcontroller.
--------------------------------------------------------------------
Q2. The size of the Flash Memory of the LPC1768 is 16Mb or 2MB. 
In GB size:
1MB has 2^20B and 1GB has 2^30B. 
Number of MB in 1 GB is 2^30/2^20 = 2^10MB/GB or 1024MB/GB. 
So, number of GB of USB Disk Flash Memory is 2^1*MB*[1GB)/(2^10MB)]
= 2MB * (1GB/1024MB)
= 0.00195 GB [USB Disk Size of LPC1768 Flash Memory]. 
--------------------------------------------------------------------
Q3. 3 Functions or Features of the mbed USB cable:
1.	To download the .bin program to the mbed board.
2.	To power the mbed board.
3.	To create files in the USB Disk for reading and writing when doing filesystem application using the mbed board.
--------------------------------------------------------------------
Q4. The name of the Ethernet PHY chip in the LPC1768 is Texas Instruments’ DP83848J PHYTER.
--------------------------------------------------------------------
Q5. The GPIO address windows are:
	0x2009,c000–0x2009,c09c and parts of 0x4002,8080-0x4002,b004
--------------------------------------------------------------------

